## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent data and the subjective nature of ethical considerations. The perspectives gathered are primarily from Western medical and legal frameworks, which may not fully represent global practices. Additionally, the complexity of individual cases means that general guidelines may not apply universally. Further research could explore cultural differences and evolving legal standards in this area.